answerText: Saturnine Poems [or Poèmes saturniens][10] This French author, the male lover of Arthur Rimbaud, wrote the Saturnine Poems.

question: Question: This collection was adapted from its author's earlier Poems and Sonnets, written in the Parnassian style. For 10 points each: [10] Name this collection of Symbolist poetry that includes the sections "Melancholia," "Paysages Tristes," and "Caprices."
